  "prompt": "How do you know you're over your relationship?",
  "response": "Here are some signs that you might be over a past relationship:\n\n1. Emotional signs\n- You no longer feel intense pain or sadness when thinking about them\n- You can talk about the relationship without emotional distress\n- You don't feel anger or resentment toward your ex\n- You're genuinely happy for their future\n\n2. Mental shifts\n- You've stopped obsessing over what went wrong\n- You're not constantly analyzing the relationship\n- You can imagine a future without them\n- You're no longer checking their social media\n\n3. Personal growth\n- You've rediscovered your individual identity\n- You're focusing on self-improvement\n- You're interested in dating or meeting new people\n- You feel more confident and independent\n\n4. Practical indicators\n- You've stopped contact or communication\n- You're not hoping for reconciliation\n- You can accept the relationship is truly over\n- You've processed your grief and healing\n\n5. Forward-looking perspectives\n- You're excited about future possibilities\n- You're open to new relationships\n- You've learned lessons from the past relationship\n- You feel peace about the situation\n\nRemember, healing is a personal journey, and everyone processes breakups differently. There's no universal timeline for getting over someone.",
